network

Class Link

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsutil.generic.state.State
      • network.Link
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Link
extends dsutil.generic.state.State
    A link has the following features: - It extends the state that is a container of information. - It has a start and end node, by default, a directed link. - It can be activated/deactivated and connected/disconnected. - It can vary the flow type: the flow can be any information contained in the state Every persistent operation over the start and end node of the link imposes a re-evaluation of the node connectivity.
